attributeList.attribute: SCF-Saf1 is a member of the SCF (Skp1-Cullin-F-box) E3 ubiquitin ligase family, in which the F-box protein, Saf1, forms the substrate recognition subunit. The complex is required for the ubiquitylation of Aah1 and several vacuolar/lysosomal enzymes. The complex may form a homodimer.
